{{Infobox cave | name = Asa Koma | photo = Pottery of Asa Koma.JPG | photo_caption = Pottery found in Asa Koma | location = Asa Koma, [[Djibouti]] | depth = <!-- Enter the deepest portion of the cave --> | length = | survey = <!--What manner of survey? What instruments were used? When was it surveyed? --> | survey_format = <!--Which cave software is it in? --> | discovery = <!--When was it discovered and by who? --> | geology = <!--What geological strata is the cave in? --> | entrance_count = <!--Number of the entrances --> | entrance_list = <!--Names of the entrances --> | difficulty = <!--Skill level required to visit the cave --> | hazards = <!--List the hazards associated with the cave --> | access = Public | translation = | language = | pronunciation = }}
'''Asa Koma''' ("Red Hill") is an [[archaeological site]] in [[Djibouti]].
==Overview== Asa Koma is an inland lake area on the Gobaad Plain. Pottery predating the mid-2nd millennium BC has been found at the site.{{When|date=July 2016}} The ware is characterized by punctate and incision geometric designs, which bear a similarity to the Sabir culture phase 1 ceramics from Ma'layba in [[Southern Arabia]].<ref name="Ohvah">{{cite book|last1=Walter Raunig|first1=Steffen Wenig|title=Afrikas Horn|date=2005|publisher=Otto Harrassowitz Verlag|isbn=3447051752|page=439|url=https://www.google.com/books?id=JpNY7VPn1WUC|accessdate=7 September 2014}}</ref> Additionally, ceramics like some of the pottery from Sihi on the Saudi coast and Subr on the Yemeni littoral have been found here.<ref name="Iuoni">{{cite book|last1=Istituto universitario orientale (Naples, Italy)|title=Annali, Volume 58|date=1998|publisher=Edizione universitarie|page=527|url=https://www.google.com/books?id=zNtiAAAAMAAJ|accessdate=15 November 2014}}</ref>
Long-horned humpless cattle bones have also been discovered at Asa Koma, suggesting that domesticated cattle was present by around 3,500 years ago.<ref name="Connah">{{cite book|last1=Connah|first1=Graham|title=Forgotten Africa: An Introduction to Its Archaeology|date=2004|publisher=Routledge|isbn=1134403038|page=46|url=https://www.google.com/books?id=ggD1wdQxBOcC|accessdate=7 September 2014}}</ref>
